summarization.results: A Catholic priest named Edmund Campion in 16th-century England bravely defended his faith despite persecution. He wrote "Campion's Brag" affirming his loyalty to Catholicism, ministered in secret, and was eventually captured, falsely accused of treason, and executed. Campion's martyrdom solidified his revered status among Catholics.
